\fs32 \cf0 \cb4 desc short simple ; dev says; Here's how the catalog planner fits this and what would need to change to support legacy vs cluster-core.\
How the catalog planner works today\
Role: Stage 1 only. It turns (topic_id, persona_id, teacher_id, brand_id) into a BookSpec. It does not choose personas, topics, or where atoms live.\
Inputs (from config):\
domain_definitions.yaml, series_templates.yaml, capacity_constraints.yaml 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  domains, series, angles\
brand_registry_locale_extension.yaml 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  locale and territory per brand (and author/narrator context)\
locale_registry.yaml 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  validate locale\
Optional author/narrator config\
Output (BookSpec):\
topic_id, persona_id, teacher_id, brand_id, series_id, installment_number, angle_id, domain_id, seed\
locale and territory from the brand (or caller)\
No field for \'93atoms model\'94 or \'93cluster vs legacy\'94\
Where personas/topics come from:\
Not from the planner. In the full-catalog flow they come from teacher_portfolio_planner: it uses canonical_personas.yaml and teachers\'92 allowed_topics (or canonical_topics.yaml) to build (teacher_id, topic_id, persona_id, brand_id). The catalog planner then only fills in angle, domain, locale, territory for that triple.\
Where atoms are chosen:\
Also not in the planner. In generate_full_catalog.py:\
If --locale-group and spec.locale are set 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  atoms_root = atoms/<locale> (e.g. atoms/zh-TW).\
Else if --atoms-root 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  use that.\
Else 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  default repo atoms/ (current persona-specific layout).\
So the planner is model-agnostic: same code path for \'93legacy\'94 and \'93cluster\'94; the split is made upstream (who gets allocated) and downstream (which atoms root and which compiler behavior).\
How this fits your legacy vs cluster-core decision\
Catalog planner itself:\
No change required for the decision. It just needs to keep emitting BookSpecs with persona_id, topic_id, locale, etc.\
What does need to reflect the split:\
Who gets allocated (personas/topics)\
Legacy EN (personas 1\'9610): Keep using the current persona list (e.g. from canonical_personas.yaml) when running the US / default brand matrix.\
Chinese / future EN 11+: Use a different persona (or archetype) source for allocation when running the ZH matrix or \'93future EN\'94 matrix, so those books are planned with cluster personas/archetypes, not the legacy 10.\
Which atoms root is used at compile time\
Legacy: atoms_root = repo atoms/ (current layout; no overlay).\
Cluster (Chinese / EN 11+): atoms_root (or an equivalent contract) points at the cluster-core layout, e.g. atoms/core/<archetype>/<topic>/<engine>/ (and later overlay resolved by compiler).\
How compile knows \'93legacy\'94 vs \'93cluster\'94\
Either:\
Derive from persona_id: e.g. config that lists \'93legacy personas\'94; if persona_id in that set 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  use repo atoms/ and current compiler; else 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  use cluster root + overlay-aware compiler, or\
Explicit on BookSpec: e.g. atoms_model: "legacy" | "cluster" (set by catalog planner or by generate_full_catalog based on persona/list). Then generate_full_catalog / run_pipeline pass the right atoms_root and the right compiler path.\
So the catalog planner doesn\'92t need to \'93know\'94 about cluster vs legacy; it only needs to be fed the right (persona, topic, brand) for each system and downstream (allocation + compile) must treat legacy and cluster differently.\
Summary\
Catalog planner: Builds BookSpec from (topic, persona, teacher, brand) and config; sets locale/territory from brand. It does not choose personas, topics, or atoms layout.\
Legacy vs cluster: Enforced by (1) which personas are used in allocation for US vs ZH vs \'93future EN\'94, and (2) which atoms_root and compiler path are used when compiling each BookSpec.\
To \'93freeze personas 1\'9610\'94 and use cluster only for Chinese and EN 11+: keep the planner as-is; add a persona list / atoms-model rule (e.g. \'93legacy personas\'94 in config) and in generate_full_catalog / run_pipeline set atoms_root and compiler behavior from that rule (or from an optional atoms_model on BookSpec set there). The planner can stay structural only; the rest of the system carries the legacy vs cluster-core policy.\cb1 \
