\fs32 \cf0 \cb4 desc simple: Here\'92s a concrete description of Cluster 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  core + overlay atoms in the compile layer.\
Cluster 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  core + overlay atoms (compile layer)\
1. What \'93atoms_root\'94 means today (legacy)\
Single root, persona-specific layout:\
atoms_root is one directory (e.g. repo atoms/ or atoms/zh-TW/).\
All resolution is atoms_root / persona_id / topic_id / \'85:\
STORY: atoms_root / persona_id / topic_id / engine / CANONICAL.txt\
Other slots: atoms_root / persona_id / topic_id / slot_type / CANONICAL.txt (REFLECTION, EXERCISE, HOOK, SCENE, INTEGRATION)\
Assembly compiler (compile_plan) gets one atoms_root, builds a PoolIndex(atoms_root=\'85), and get_pool(slot_type, persona_id, topic_id) reads from that single tree.\
Prose resolver (resolve_prose_for_plan) gets the same atoms_root and, for each engine and slot type, does atoms_root / ctx.persona_id / ctx.topic_id / \'85 to load prose.\
So today: one root, one layout, persona = first path segment.\
2. What \'93atoms_root\'94 means for cluster (core + overlay)\
For cluster you move to two logical roots (and possibly two path shapes):\
Core: shared by archetype (e.g. 4 archetypes \'d7 topics \'d7 engines). No persona in the path.\
Overlay: persona-specific fragments that customize or replace parts of the core.\
So \'93atoms_root\'94 in the API can stay one physical root (e.g. atoms/ or atoms/zh/), but under that root the layout and resolution rules change when in \'93cluster mode\'94:\
Core path pattern: e.g. atoms/core/<archetype>/<topic>/<engine>/CANONICAL.txt (STORY) and atoms/core/<archetype>/<topic>/<slot_type>/CANONICAL.txt (others).\
Overlay path pattern: e.g. atoms/overlay/<persona>/<engine>/fragments.txt (or per-slot overlays). Persona maps to one archetype (config).\
So:\
Which atoms_root is used:\
For cluster, you still pass one root (e.g. atoms/ or a dedicated atoms/zh/). That root is expected to contain both core/ and overlay/ (or equivalent) and the cluster compiler interprets paths under that root differently from legacy.\
Which compiler path runs:\
A cluster-aware code path that:\
Resolves (persona_id, topic_id) 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  archetype_id (config).\
Loads core atoms by (archetype_id, topic_id, engine/slot_type).\
Loads overlay atoms by (persona_id, engine/slot_type) (and optionally topic if you add it).\
Merges/overrides: e.g. core pool first, then overlay fragments applied at defined insertion points (see below).\
3. Directory layout (cluster, under one root)\
Under the single atoms_root used for cluster:\
atoms_root/  core/    <archetype_id>/           # e.g. anxious_professional, burned_out_caretaker, ...      <topic_id>/             # anxiety, boundaries, grief, ...        <engine>/             # shame, false_alarm, overwhelm, ...          CANONICAL.txt       # STORY blocks (same block format as today)        REFLECTION/          CANONICAL.txt        EXERCISE/          CANONICAL.txt        HOOK/        SCENE/        INTEGRATION/        ...  overlay/    <persona_id>/             # e.g. gen_z_tw, burned_out_professional_tw      <engine>/               # or per-slot_type        fragments.yaml        # or fragments.txt: overlay blocks, insertion rules      REFLECTION/        fragments.yaml      ...\
Core: one set of CANONICAL.txt per (archetype, topic, engine/slot). Shared by all personas that map to that archetype.\
Overlay: per-persona, per-engine (or per-slot_type) fragments that get injected into the core pool or prose at compile time.\
So: atoms_root is still one directory; cluster means \'93under this root, use core/ + overlay/ and the cluster resolution rules.\'94\
4. Which compiler path runs (cluster vs legacy)\
Conceptually:\
Legacy path (personas 1\'9610, EN):\
atoms_root = repo atoms/ (or locale-specific atoms/zh-TW/ if you ever use it for legacy).\
Single-path resolution: atoms_root / persona_id / topic_id / engine|slot_type / CANONICAL.txt.\
Same assembly_compiler.compile_plan + pool_index.PoolIndex(atoms_root=\'85) + prose_resolver.resolve_prose_for_plan(atoms_root=\'85) as today. No core/overlay.\
Cluster path (Chinese, EN 11+):\
atoms_root = same repo root or a dedicated root that contains core/ and overlay/.\
Dual-path resolution:\
Resolve persona_id 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  archetype_id (from config, e.g. persona_archetype_mapping.yaml or inside locale/brand config).\
Core: load from atoms_root / "core" / archetype_id / topic_id / engine|slot_type / CANONICAL.txt.\
Overlay: load from atoms_root / "overlay" / persona_id / engine|slot_type / fragments.*.\
So a different (or extended) code path: either a cluster-aware PoolIndex (or a wrapper that builds pools from core + overlay) and a cluster-aware prose resolver that applies overlay fragments at defined points.\
So:\
Legacy: one compiler path, one layout, one root.\
Cluster: one root, but a second compiler path (or same entrypoint with a \'93cluster mode\'94 flag) that uses core + overlay layout and resolution.\
5. Where overlay injection happens (insertion points)\
Overlay can attach at two levels (both in the same \'93cluster\'94 path):\
A. Pool construction (Stage 3 \'96 assembly compiler)\
Core pool: build list of AtomEntry from core CANONICAL.txt (by archetype, topic, engine/slot).\
Overlay: load overlay fragments (e.g. YAML with atom_id, body, insertion_rule).\
Insertion rules can be:\
Replace: overlay atom replaces a core atom with same role/band/semantic_family.\
Append: overlay atom is added to the pool (so it can be selected like any other).\
Prefer: if overlay has an atom for (role, band), prefer it over core when resolving that slot.\
So the cluster PoolIndex (or equivalent) returns a merged pool: core + overlay, with overlay applied according to these rules. The rest of the slot resolver (deterministic selection, no reuse, band/semantic_family rules) stays the same; it just sees a larger/merged pool.\
B. Prose resolution (Stage 6 \'96 prose resolver)\
Core prose: from core/<archetype>/<topic>/<engine|slot>/CANONICAL.txt (same block parsing as today).\
Overlay prose: from overlay/<persona>/<engine|slot>/fragments.*.\
Merge: for each atom_id that was selected in the plan, prose can come from core or overlay. If the plan\'92s atom_id was chosen from an overlay entry (during Stage 3), Stage 6 already has that atom_id in the overlay prose map. If the rule is \'93replace by same role/band,\'94 the plan might still use core atom_ids but Stage 6 could substitute overlay prose for that role/band when overlay exists (that would require Stage 6 to know \'93this atom_id is from core but has an overlay override for this persona\'94).\
So:\
Cleanest: overlay is represented as real atoms in the pool (with their own atom_ids). Then injection is \'93at pool build time\'94: overlay atoms are merged into the pool; selection is unchanged; prose is resolved by atom_id from core or overlay. No special \'93seam\'94 logic beyond normal block parsing.\
Alternative: overlay as \'93prose override\'94 only: same atom_id as core, but body from overlay. That would require the resolver to know persona and overlay path and prefer overlay prose when present.\
6. End-to-end cluster compile flow (which atoms_root, which path)\
Caller (e.g. generate_full_catalog / run_pipeline)\
Decides \'93this book is cluster\'94 (e.g. by persona list or BookSpec flag).\
Sets atoms_root (e.g. repo atoms/ or atoms/zh/).\
Calls the cluster compile path (e.g. compile_plan(..., atoms_model="cluster") or a separate compile_plan_cluster(...)).\
Cluster compile path\
Loads persona_id 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  archetype_id from config.\
Uses atoms_root as the base for both:\
Core: atoms_root / "core" / archetype_id / topic_id / ...\
Overlay: atoms_root / "overlay" / persona_id / ...\
Builds pools (STORY and other slots) by merging core + overlay per the rules above.\
Runs the same slot_resolver and chapter/band logic as today; only the pool is different.\
Writes CompiledBook (same schema); atom_ids may now include overlay-origin ids.\
Prose resolution (cluster)\
Same atoms_root.\
For each atom_id in the plan, resolve prose from:\
Overlay first (if that atom_id came from overlay), else\
Core (by archetype, topic, engine/slot).\
Seam smoothing: if you do phrase-level injection (e.g. locale-specific phrases), that can be a post-pass or a dedicated \'93seam\'94 pass in the renderer using the same overlay config.\
Viability / gates\
Tuple viability (and any other gates) would need a cluster mode: check core pools (and optionally overlay) under atoms_root/core/<archetype>/... instead of atoms_root/<persona>/....\
7. Summary table (cluster vs legacy)\
Concern	Legacy (personas 1\'9610)	Cluster (Chinese, EN 11+)\
atoms_root	Single root (e.g. atoms/ or atoms/zh-TW/)	Same single root; layout under it is core/ + overlay/\
Path shape	atoms_root / persona_id / topic_id / engine|slot_type / CANONICAL.txt	Core: atoms_root / core / archetype_id / topic_id / ...; Overlay: atoms_root / overlay / persona_id / ...\
Who resolves persona	persona_id is the first path segment	persona_id 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  archetype_id (config); core uses archetype_id, overlay uses persona_id\
Pool construction	PoolIndex from one tree (persona/topic/slot)	Cluster pool builder: core pool + overlay merge (replace/append/prefer)\
Compiler path	Current compile_plan + PoolIndex + resolve_prose	Cluster path: same entrypoint with cluster flag, or separate function; uses core+overlay PoolIndex and cluster-aware prose resolution\
Prose resolution	atoms_root / persona / topic / engineslot 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  CANONICAL.txt	Core prose by (archetype, topic, engineslot); overlay prose by (persona, engineslot); merge by atom_id or override rule\
Gates	Viability checks atoms_root / persona / topic / engine	Viability checks atoms_root / core / archetype / topic / engine (and optionally overlay depth)\
So for \'93Cluster 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  core + overlay atoms\'94 in the compile layer: you keep one atoms_root; you add a second resolution and compiler path that, under that root, uses core (by archetype) and overlay (by persona) and merges them at pool build time (and optionally at prose resolution time) with clear insertion points and no change to legacy personas 1\'9610.\cb1 \
