Enforce "personas 1\'9610 = legacy (persona-specific atoms), Chinese / EN 11+ = cluster (core + overlay)" by:\
\
\
\
\
\
Config: Define which personas are legacy; optionally define cluster persona source for allocation.\
\
\
\
Allocation: Use legacy persona list for US/default matrix; allow a different persona source when running ZH or future-EN matrix.\
\
\
\
BookSpec / compile: Add optional atoms_model; downstream sets atoms_root and (later) compiler path from it.\
\
Catalog planner stays unchanged; allocation and compile layers carry the policy.\
\
\
\
1. Config: legacy personas and atoms model\
\
New file: config/catalog_planning/atoms_model.yaml\
\
\
\
\
\
legacy_personas: list of persona_ids (the 10 from canonical_personas.yaml). Used to derive atoms_model for a given persona_id and to document "locked legacy" in one place.\
\
\
\
Optional: cluster_personas_file (e.g. canonical_personas_cluster.yaml) for allocation when running cluster catalog; if absent, cluster allocation can still use the same canonical list until you add ZH-specific personas/archetypes.\
\
Schema shape (minimal):\
\
# atoms_model.yaml \'97 legacy vs cluster policy (compile + allocation)\
schema_version: 1\
legacy_personas:\
  - millennial_women_professionals\
  - tech_finance_burnout\
  # ... (all 10 from canonical_personas.yaml)\
cluster_personas_file: null   # optional; e.g. canonical_personas_cluster.yaml\
\
Loader: Add a small helper (e.g. in phoenix_v4/planning/ or in scripts/generate_full_catalog.py) to load this YAML and expose is_legacy_persona(persona_id) and optionally get_cluster_personas_path().\
\
\
\
2. Allocation: persona source per catalog type\
\
Current behavior: teacher_portfolio_planner.py always uses _load_canonical_personas() (reads canonical_personas.yaml) for persona_list in allocate_wave().\
\
Change: Add an optional parameter to allocate_wave():\
\
\
\
\
\
personas_override: Optional[list[str]] = None \'97 if provided, use this list instead of _load_canonical_personas(). If None, keep current behavior (canonical_personas.yaml).\
\
Caller: generate_full_catalog.py\
\
\
\
\
\
When running with default brand matrix (US): call allocate_wave(..., personas_override=None) 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  legacy personas from canonical_personas.yaml.\
\
\
\
When running with --brand-matrix config/catalog_planning/brand_teacher_matrix_zh.yaml (or a future EN cluster matrix): if atoms_model.yaml has cluster_personas_file, load that file and pass personas_override=that_list; else pass None (keep using canonical list until you add a dedicated cluster persona list).\
\
This keeps allocation for ZH/future-EN explicitly tied to a configurable persona source without changing the planner.\
\
\
\
3. BookSpec: optional atoms_model\
\
Change in: phoenix_v4/planning/catalog_planner.py\
\
\
\
\
\
Add to BookSpec dataclass: atoms_model: Optional[str] = None (allowed values "legacy" | "cluster"). Do not set it inside produce_single(); the planner stays agnostic.\
\
\
\
In to_dict(), include atoms_model in the output when it is not None (so persisted .spec.json and compiled plan can carry it).\
\
Who sets it: The caller that knows catalog type (e.g. generate_full_catalog), not the planner. So either:\
\
\
\
\
\
Option A (recommended): generate_full_catalog, after building each spec via planner.produce_single(...), sets spec.atoms_model (requires a mutable spec or a small helper that returns a spec dict with atoms_model added). If BookSpec is a dataclass, add a line after the loop: e.g. set spec.atoms_model = "legacy" if spec.persona_id in legacy_personas else "cluster" (need to load legacy list once per run).\
\
\
\
Option B: Catalog planner\'92s produce_single() accepts optional atoms_model: Optional[str] = None and passes it through. generate_full_catalog then passes atoms_model=... when calling produce_single() (derived from persona_id + legacy list). This avoids mutating the spec after creation.\
\
Recommend Option B so the planner remains a pure function of (topic, persona, teacher, brand, \'85) and the caller supplies the policy flag.\
\
Contract: In specs/OMEGA_LAYER_CONTRACTS.md, add atoms_model under Stage 1 
\f7 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Stage 2 as an optional identity/passthrough field: "legacy" | "cluster"; when absent, downstream may derive from config.\
\
\
\
4. generate_full_catalog: set atoms_model and atoms_root per spec\
\
Changes in: scripts/generate_full_catalog.py\
\
\
\
\
\
Load atoms_model.yaml once (or the legacy_personas list). Expose a helper that returns atoms_model for a given persona_id (legacy if in list, else cluster).\
\
\
\
When building BookSpecs: Call planner.produce_single(..., atoms_model=atoms_model_for(alloc.persona_id)). That requires passing atoms_model into produce_single() (Option B above).\
\
\
\
When calling run_pipeline (compile step):\
\
\
\
\
\
Compute atoms_model for this spec (from spec.atoms_model if set, else from persona_id + legacy list).\
\
\
\
Legacy: atoms_root = None (default repo atoms/). Do not pass --atoms-root unless --locale-group is used for a legacy locale (current behavior can stay as-is for legacy).\
\
\
\
Cluster: atoms_root = args.atoms_root or str(REPO_ROOT / "atoms") (or a dedicated cluster root like REPO_ROOT / "atoms_cluster" if you want a separate tree). Pass --atoms-root and --atoms-model cluster so run_pipeline and the compiler can use the cluster path when implemented.\
\
\
\
Plan-only: When writing .spec.json, include atoms_model in the dict (from spec), so a later compile that reads the spec file has the flag.\
\
Persona source for allocation: When brand_matrix_path points at the ZH matrix (or a path you designate as \'93cluster\'94), load cluster persona list from atoms_model.yaml\'92s cluster_personas_file if present and pass personas_override=... to allocate_wave(). Otherwise pass None.\
\
\
\
5. run_pipeline: accept and pass atoms_model\
\
Changes in: scripts/run_pipeline.py\
\
\
\
\
\
Add CLI argument: --atoms-model with choices legacy | cluster, default legacy.\
\
\
\
Resolve effective atoms_model: If --atoms-model is set, use it. Else if the book spec (from planner or from --input YAML) contains atoms_model, use that. Else derive from config: load atoms_model.yaml, if persona_id in legacy_personas then legacy else cluster.\
\
\
\
Pass atoms_model into compile_plan() (add parameter to phoenix_v4/planning/assembly_compiler.py compile_plan(..., atoms_model: Optional[str] = None)). When atoms_model == "cluster", pass the same or a dedicated atoms_root; the compiler will use it when cluster resolution is implemented (no change to pool resolution in this plan).\
\
\
\
Ensure book_spec_for_compiler includes atoms_model when set (from BookSpec or from CLI), so the written plan JSON carries it for downstream (e.g. render, QA).\
\
\
\
6. assembly_compiler: accept atoms_model (no behavior change yet)\
\
Changes in: phoenix_v4/planning/assembly_compiler.py\
\
\
\
\
\
Add atoms_model: Optional[str] = None to compile_plan(). Use only for passing through to any future cluster pool index; for this plan, do not change pool resolution. Legacy and cluster both use the existing atoms_root and PoolIndex path. This step only adds the parameter and documents that when atoms_model == "cluster", a future implementation will switch to core+overlay resolution.\
\
\
\
7. Optional: persist atoms_model in compiled plan\
\
In run_pipeline, when writing the output plan JSON, include atoms_model in the top-level plan (e.g. under book_spec or a sibling field) so that Stage 6 (prose resolver) or other consumers can branch on legacy vs cluster if needed. This is a single field write where the plan is assembled (same place as locale, territory, etc.).\
\
